[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hate crime: 'Calling me filthy, dirty tranny'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Evie Heston, from Kent, who is transgender, was abused and threatened by her neighbour in November 2014.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
17 November 2015 Last updated at 14:41 GMT
In March, a woman pleaded guilty to using threatening, abusive, insulting words or behaviour intended to cause harassment, alarm and distress.
She was given an 18-month conditional discharge.
Ms Heston spoke to BBC Radio Kent after figures showed almost 1,000 hate crimes were reported to Kent Police in the past year.
